dcterms:description: The Tennessee-Eastman (TE) chemical process simulates a real chemical production process and includes one normal state and 20 fault states. It is widely used as a benchmark process to evaluate fault detection and fault diagnosis methods.
dcterms:title: Tennessee-Eastman (TE) Dataset

dcterms:description: The KDD-CUP99 dataset recorded 7 million network traffic connection records over 7 weeks, labeled as normal or attacked data, and is used for evaluating intrusion detection systems.
dcterms:title: KDD-CUP99 Dataset

dcterms:description: The Proton Exchange Membrane Fuel Cell (PEMFC) dataset simulates a real fuel cell system, consisting of 6 single cells, with features including voltages of the cells and various fault conditions.
dcterms:title: Proton Exchange Membrane Fuel Cell (PEMFC) Dataset

dcterms:description: The Wheelset Bearing Dataset (WHELL) simulates high-speed rail wheelset bearings under various loading conditions, with data collected from sensors to analyze fault states.
dcterms:title: Wheelset Bearing Dataset (WHELL)
